President Biden and Taoiseach Varadkar of Ireland held a bilateral meeting at the White House ahead of a St. Patrick's Day celebration. They discussed the strong ties between the United States and Ireland, as well as their shared commitment to supporting Ukraine against Russian aggression. President Biden praised the generosity of the Irish people in hosting refugees from the conflict in Ukraine. The leaders also talked about their cooperation on various global issues. They reaffirmed their support for the Belfast/Good Friday Agreement and welcomed the Windsor Framework as a way to preserve its peace dividend. They also discussed trade, investment, and measures to strengthen the resilience of their economies.